results.name: Expansion of eta(q)*eta(q^2)*eta(q^18)^2/(eta(q^6)*eta(q^9)) in powers of q.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
formula: Multiplicative with a(2^e) = (-1)^e, a(3^e) = -2 if e>0, a(p^e) = e+1 if p == 1 (mod 6), a(p^e) = (1+(-1)^e)/2 if p == 5 (mod 6).
mathematica: QP = QPochhammer; s = QP[q]*QP[q^2]*(QP[q^18]^2/(QP[q^6]*QP[q^9])) + O[q]^100; CoefficientList[s, q] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 25 2015 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n)=local(A); if (n<1, 0, n--; A=x*O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x+A)*eta(x^2+A)*eta(x^18+A)^2/ eta(x^6+A)/eta(x^9+A), n))}
